Package teal.sim.properties

Provides interfaces for Simulation objects physical and EM properties.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ForceModel
    Objects that represent a force.
    HasAcceleration
    WorldObjects that have an acceleration should implement this interface.
    HasCollisionDetection
    Currently a very simple interface to handle collisions, note any physical object may collide but only classes which implement this will do the checking.
    HasFieldLines  
    HasMass
    WorldObjects that have Mass (M) should implement HasMass Implementing this interface allows read / write access to your mass property.
    HasMomentOfInertia
    All EM objects which have Moment Of Inertia should implement this interface.
    HasVelocity
    WorldObjects that move around (have velocity) should implement this interface.
    IsSpatial
    All EM objects which have a point charge should implement this interface.
    PhysicalElement  
    Stepping
    SimElements implementing the Stepping interface will have their nextStep() method called by the SimEngine at each frame of the simulation.

Package teal.sim.properties Description

Provides interfaces for Simulation objects physical and EM properties. This sentence is here to prevent errors when generating javadocs.
